11 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Subsection 1 of section 54-10-15 of the North Dakota Century
12 Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
13 1. The state auditor, by duly appointed deputy auditors or other authorized agents, shall
14 audit or review the books, records, and financial accounts of any political subdivision
15 when ordered by the legislative audit and fiscal review committee. The state auditor,
16 by duly appointed auditors or other authorized agents, may audit or review the books,
17 records, and financial accounts of any political subdivisions when requested by the
18 governor, requested by the governing board, or upon petition of at least thirty-five
19 percent of the qualified electors of any political subdivision enumerated in section
20 54-10-14 voting for the office of governor at the preceding general election or, in the
21 case ofregarding school districts, upon petition of at least thirty-five percent of the
22 qualified electors voting at the preceding school board election, regarding water
23 districts subject to chapter 61 - 35, upon a petition of at least ten percent or three
24 hundred participating members, whichever is fewer, or upon the request of the state
25 court administrator with respect to clerk of district court services provided by a county
26 in accordance with chapter 27-05.2. Fees for the audits must be paid in accordance
27 with the provisions of section 54-10-14.
