1 2. At the annual meeting in each year after the year in which the district is organized, a
2 director must be elected to succeed each director whose term of office expires on that
3 date, and each director so elected holds office for a term of three years and until a
4 successor is elected and has qualified.
5 3. Vacancies must be filled for the unexpired term by appointment by the remaining
6 directors until the next annual meeting of participating members, at which the
7 participating members shall elect a director for the unexpired term.
8 4. All elections held under this chapter must be conducted to allow participating members
9 to access all stages of the election process, including voting and vote tabulation in a
10 uniform and nondiscriminatory manner. Each meeting must be arranged in a manner
11 that permits each participating member to plainly observe the election process.
